Great. For me I’d just say 
.stick-header{
position: sticky;
top: 0;
}

It does the magic with less css codes

I used this for the js: 
const header = document.querySelectorAll('.small');
const stickyHeader = document.querySelector('.sticky-header')

window.addEventListener("scroll", function(e) {
    let scroll = this.scrollY;
    if(scroll > 80) {
         header.forEach(head => head.style.display = "none");
         stickyHeader.style.height = "100px";
     } else {
          stickyHeader.style.height = "180px"
          header.forEach(head => head.style.display = "inherit");
       }
});
(have to give small tag a class to select them)
